<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/891204bc7ad6e4bf43e1b3a6303e2c6e.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 9 and b = 8. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>12.0</li><li>48.4</li><li>41.6</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}^{{2}}+{8}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={81}+{64}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={145}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{145}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{12.041594578792}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{12}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{9}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{48.36646066343}\approx{48.4}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{48.36646066343}^{\circ}\approx{41.63353933657}\approx{41.6}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

